#           (Yang Jianlin "yjl9903" — TypeScript developer,
#           Anime + ACG-tooling open-source author)
#
#  Source-direct extraction from
#    https://github.com/yjl9903/AnimeSpace/blob/main/apps/animespace/src/cli.ts
#      (breadc CLI builder with middleware + command groups)
#    https://github.com/yjl9903/AnimeSpace/blob/main/apps/animespace/package.json (bin: anime, animespace)
#    https://github.com/yjl9903/Breadc (the yjl9903/Breadc library
#    — also by yjl9903; co-released with AnimeSpace)
#
#  Maintained by yjl9903 (Yang Jianlin, Chinese TypeScript
#  developer focused on Anime/ACG tooling).  yjl9903/AnimeSpace:
#  87 GH stars.  AnimeSpace is "Keep following your favourite
#  anime" — a CLI for ANIME ENTHUSIASTS who track currently-
#  airing series across multiple seasons.  Workflow: define
#  watch list in a config file (or import from Bangumi.tv
#  collection), then run `anime watch` periodically to:
#  (1) query Bangumi.tv for episode metadata, (2) query AnimeGarden
#  for new BT/magnet resources matching the show, (3) download
#  matched episodes via aria2 or qBittorrent, (4) optionally
#  upload to S3 / WebDAV / local NAS for cloud storage.  Used
#  by anime fans + ACG community as an alternative to Sonarr's
#  TV-focused workflow that doesn't handle anime's per-season
#  release schedule well.  Sister tools: Sonarr (TV automation
#  for general TV — in corpus via _sonarr; the Western-TV
#  equivalent), radarr (movie automation — in corpus via
#  _radarr), aria2 (download manager — in corpus + STOCK),
#  qbittorrent (BT client — in corpus + STOCK), transmission
#  (BT client — in corpus + STOCK).  ACG-specific siblings:
#  AnimeGarden (yjl9903's BT-resource aggregator), Bangumi.tv
#  (the Chinese anime database, ACG-equivalent of MAL/AniList),
#  anitomy (anime filename parser by Eren Okka — IN CORPUS via
#  _anitomy).
